description:
¬øC√≥mo analizar la tecnica de carrera de velocidad?: desglosa la carrera!!üëåüèº
Me encuentro estudiando el curso universitario: Entrenamiento de la Velocidad de la Teor√≠a a la Pr√°ctica en @techuniversidad üìöüôáüèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
Y me gustaria compartir con ustedes una herramienta visual y anal√≠tica utilizada para evaluar y mejorar la t√©cnica en las fases clave de la carrera de velocidad: kinograma de altis. 
@Altis (centro especializado en el tema) propone realizar un kinograma: kinograma es b√°sicamente pausar un video en determinados cuadros y sacar una imagen. ‚òùüèº
Este modelo se centra en descomponer la carrera en fases espec√≠ficas para identificar detalles t√©cnicos que pueden optimizarse. Y se dividen en:

‚ú®Toe-off: ultimo cuadro antes que el pie de la pierna de apoyo abandone el suelo.
‚ú®MVP: la altura m√°xima de la proyecci√≥n vertical, definida por la posici√≥n en la que ambos pies est√°n en paralelo al piso.
‚ú®Strike: se define cuando el muslo opuesto a la pierna adelantada est√° perpendicular al piso.
‚ú®Touch-down: el primer cuadro donde el pie de la pierna del swing golpea el suelo.
‚ú®Full support: el cuadro en donde el pie est√° directamente debajo de la pelvis.

El an√°lisis detallado de cada una de estas fases permite a los entrenadores y atletas identificar √°reas de mejora y ajustar la t√©cnica de carrera. Esto puede incluir cambios en la postura, la mec√°nica del brazo, la eficiencia de la zancada y el manejo de la fatiga, lo cual puede llevar a mejoras significativas en el rendimiento de los velocistas. üèÉüèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èüí®
‚ÄºÔ∏èEs importante recordar que cada atleta presenta una estructura antropom√©trica √∫nica, capacidades f√≠sicas y patrones de movimiento asimilados de forma diferente. Por lo tanto, existe una variabilidad importante dentro de estas formas.‚ÄºÔ∏è

Ahora que sabes esto‚Ä¶. Gr√°bate y analiza tus carreras üëèüèΩ

description:
üí• The hanging bridge on the Carstensz Pyramid, at 4,800 meters on the ridge near the summit, is one of the most exciting and challenging parts of the climb. It is a bridge made of steel cables, suspended between two large rock pillars, crossing a deep abyss at a great height. The bridge is narrow, with only one cable for your feet and two more at shoulder height to help you maintain balance as you move forward. The sensation of the void beneath your feet and the exposure to the wind make this crossing especially dizzying. It‚Äôs both a physical and mental test on the way to the summit.
Using my @goflexi boots üí™üèª

ü•æ @flexicountry #CaminandoJuntos

üì∑ @gopromx #Hero13

El puente colgante en la Pir√°mide de Carstensz  a 4,800m ya en el risco cerca de la cumbre, es una de las partes m√°s emocionantes y desafiantes de la escalada. Se trata de un puente hecho de cables de acero, suspendido entre dos grandes pilares de roca, que cruza un profundo abismo a gran altura. El puente es angosto, con solo un cable en los que apoyas los pies y otros dos m√°s a la altura de los hombros para mantener el equilibrio mientras avanzas. La sensaci√≥n de vac√≠o bajo tus pies y la exposici√≥n al viento hacen que este cruce sea especialmente vertiginoso. Es una prueba tanto f√≠sica como mental en el camino hacia la cima.

- 1/2 red bell pepper diced (seeds out)
- 1 piece of cucumber diced
- 1/4 red onion diced
- 1 mango diced 
- juice of 2-3 limes
- salt to taste
COCONUT RICE
- 1 1/2 cups coconut milk mixed with 1 1/2 cups of water
- salt to taste
- 3 cups of jasmine rice (rinsed) 
SALMON
- skin on or skinless salmon filets
- oil of choice 
- lawrys seasoning salt
- black pepper
- brown sugar
- onion powder
- garlic powder
- smoked paprika
- dried parsley flakes 
SRIRACHA MAYO
- kewpie mayo
- sriracha to taste
- 1 tbsp of Thai sweet chili sauce 

directions:
- dice all the salsa ingredients and add them to a bowl with lime juice. season with salt to taste and set in the fridge while you get the rest of the dinner ready
- add coconut milk, water and salt to a small pot and bring to a light boil. once boiling, add rinsed rice and cover. bring heat down to low and cook covered for 18 minutes. once 18 minutes is up, remove pot from heat (still keep the lid on) and allow to sit for 5 minutes. fluff rice after 5 minutes 
- coat all sides of salmon with oil. season all sides with seasonings listed above. add salmon filets to oiled air fryer basket and spray with more oil on top. air fry at 375 for 10 minutes 
- for sriracha mayo on top of salmon, mix kewpie mayo along with your desired amount of sriracha and 1 tbsp of Thai sweet chili sauce. thin out the mayo with some water if needed 
- plate salmon to your liking and enjoy! üòã

description:
Happy Air FryDay! Lamb Chops Recipe üêëüç¥

Ingredients:

1 rack of lamb, trimmed
1/3 cup or so Dijon vinaigrette (homemade or any store-bought Italian salad dressing you like)

Instructions:

1. Pat the rack of lamb dry with a paper towel and trim any excess fat.
2. Slice between each rib to create individual lamb chops.
4. Marinate in Dijon vinaigrette for at least 1 hour, or overnight for extra flavor.
5. Let the lamb come to room temperature before cooking, 20-30 minutes if you have the time. 
6. Preheat the air fryer to 400¬∞F (200¬∞C). Air fry the lamb chops for 3 minutes on each side for medium-rare, or adjust to your preferred doneness. Discard the left behind marinade the chops were in. 
7. Serve with roasted potatoes and a fresh salad. Enjoy!

description:
BLUEBERRY DOUGH RECIPE ‚¨áÔ∏è

I don‚Äôt know about you, but I always buy the large container of blueberries‚Ä¶ with so much hope in my soul that I‚Äôll eat them all. I never do. I had some left in the fridge that were getting close to the end, so I used them in pasta dough! 

They give off a beautiful color and you still get some of the nutrients from the berries.

THE GOODS:
1 cup 00 or all purpose flour 
1 large egg 
1/4 cup blueberry syrup 

* To make the syrup, cook blueberries, tbsp of sugar, squeeze of lemon juice and just enough water to loosen them up. 
* Allow to cook down until soft and allow to cool. 
* Strain the syrup to get any clumps out, or you can pulse in the food processor. 

Enjoy!

XO,
Peace, love and #pasta

description:
For Valentine‚Äôs Day, I‚Äôm all about neutral decor, so I decided to create these adorable moss heart topiaries. They‚Äôre incredibly easy to make and look perfect sitting on a shelf or even your kitchen countertop. Here‚Äôs what you‚Äôll need:

ü§ç Sticks (cut to varying lengths)
ü§ç Flower pots or other containers 
ü§ç Grapevine heart wreaths 
ü§ç Moss
ü§ç Mod Podge
ü§ç Hot glue gun

Start by cutting the sticks to staggered lengths and hot glue the grapevine hearts onto them. Next, apply a generous amount of Mod Podge to each heart and press the moss onto it, covering it completely. To create the base, fill a flower pot with floral foam and insert the stick into the foam. For added stability, place some rocks in the pot, then top everything off with more moss.

I absolutely love how these turned out‚Äîdon‚Äôt you?

Comment ‚Äúheart‚Äù and I‚Äôll DM you all the links to make your own!

INGREDIENTS¬†
* 1 Egg
* 1 teaspoon Vanilla Extract
* ¬º cup Flaxseed Meal
* ¬Ω -3/4 teaspoon Baking Powder
* 2 teaspoons unsweetened organic Applesauce (this doesn‚Äôt make it taste sweet, just balanced the flavor)
INSTRUCTIONS
* Combine all ingredients in bowl

* Wait 1 minute to cool

description:
Sourdough Bread 

INGREDIENTS
* 100 grams, sourdough starter
* 300 grams of warm water
* 500 grams of bread flour
* 10 grams of sea salts
* 75 grams of warm water

Instructions: 

Make the dough: Whisk the starter and water together in a large bowl with a fork or spatula. Add the flour and salt. Mix to combine, finishing by hand if necessary to form a rough dough. Cover with a damp towel and let rest for 30 minutes.¬†

Stretch and fold: After 30 minutes, grab a corner of the dough and pull it up and into the center. Repeat until you‚Äôve performed this series of folds 4 to 5 times with the dough. Let dough rest for another 30 minutes and repeat the stretching and folding action. 

Shape: Coax the dough onto a lightly floured surface. Gently shape it into a round: fold the top down to the center, turn the dough, fold the top down to the center, turn the dough; repeat until you‚Äôve come full circle. 

Rest: Meanwhile, line an 8-inch (20-cm) bowl or proofing basket with a towel and dust with flour. Using a bench scraper or your hands, shape it again as described in step 4. Place the round into your lined bowl, seam side up.

Proof: Cover the dough and room temperature for 24 hours. Place a Dutch oven in your oven, and preheat your oven to 500F. Cut a piece of parchment to fit the size of your baking pot.

Score: Place the parchment over the dough and invert the bowl to release. Using the tip of a small knife or a razor blade, score the dough however you wish ‚Äî a simple ‚ÄúX‚Äù is nice. Use the parchment to carefully transfer the dough into the preheated baking pot.

Bake: Lower the oven to temperature to 450¬∫F. Carefully cover the pot. Bake the dough for 30 minutes, covered. Remove the lid, lower the temperature to 400¬∫F and continue to bake for 20 minutes more. lift the loaf out of the pot, and bake directly on the oven rack for the last 5 to 10 minutes. Cool on a wire rack for 1 hour before slicing. Enjoy your meal.

description:
Item Cafe is the newest addition to Downtown Lynn. They are a breath of fresh air to the neighborhood. Focusing more on craft coffees, teas & lattes that you can enjoy in a spacious, relaxing, laid back setting. The perfect place to meet your friends on a weekend morning, or work remotely. Bring your laptop & headphones and get to work with a fresh coffee by your side. Linda is passionate about what she does. Her beans are locally sourced & her pastries come from local bakeries. She does her own sandwiches as well, vegan & non vegan options. She said she plans on doing more with the food when she becomes more established. For now, the coffee is the selling point and that‚Äôs what she intends to focus on. 

Linda sent us half the menu! The cold brew was perfect. The toasted marshmallow latte was delicious as well. And that blue croissant was very unique. Fresh, flaky croissant and the blue spread made with cashews & spirulina gave off sort of a vanilla taste. I feel that Linda & Item Cafe will do great at this location. I love being a Downtown Lynn resident. So many great spots to check out & this one fits perfectly. Come by & tell Linda who sent you. And thanks to Lynn Main Streets. Be sure to follow them!

description:
**üìñ Scoring Sourdough: The Secret to a Perfect Ear! ü•ñ** 

Did you know the *angle* at which you score your sourdough can make or break that beautiful ‚Äúear‚Äù that looks like it‚Äôs right out of a bakery! üåü 

It‚Äôs not just about making your bread look fancy‚Äîit‚Äôs about helping your dough expand in all the right ways for the perfect bake. 

Here‚Äôs the breakdown for success: 

üî™ **Why the Angle Matters** 
Scoring at a 45-degree angle creates a flap of dough that rises and crisps up beautifully, forming that signature ear. A vertical cut (90 degrees) will expand but won‚Äôt give you that dramatic lift or texture. 

üí° **Tips for Scoring Like a Pro** 
1Ô∏è‚É£ Use a sharp lame or razor blade‚Äîclean cuts = clean rise. 
2Ô∏è‚É£ Chill your dough before scoring for better control.  I actually chill mine for 8-10 hours for the final rise instead of on the counter. 
3Ô∏è‚É£ Aim for ¬º to ¬Ω inch depth to allow proper expansion. 
4Ô∏è‚É£ Score confidently. Wobbly hands = uneven results. 
5Ô∏è‚É£ Practice makes perfect! Every bake teaches you something new. üíï

Because scoring at the right angle doesn‚Äôt just create art‚Äîit‚Äôs functional! A well-scored loaf bakes evenly, prevents blowouts, and makes every crumb as dreamy as it should be. 

‚û°Ô∏è **SHARE** this with your sourdough-loving friends and let‚Äôs spread the love for bread art! üçû 

If you are wanting to get started with making sourdough definitely follow along @momsdinnerbell. I‚Äôve only been making it for 2 months and have learned so much already.  I‚Äôm going to continue documenting my journey.

description:
I jumped on the #weightedvest bandwagon! Here‚Äôs why as a woman over age 40 I am excited about this! 

Added weight from a weighted vest can: 

Improve Bone Density:
Weighted vests can help offset age-related bone loss by applying additional stress to bones during weight-bearing activities. This promotes stronger bone formation and decreases the risk of osteoporosis.

Enhance Strength and Muscle Tone:
Adding extra resistance to bodyweight exercises like squats or push-ups promotes muscle growth, which is essential for maintaining strength and metabolism as we age.

Boost Cardiovascular Fitness and Calorie Burn:
Wearing a vest during walking, hiking, or jogging increases the intensity of the activity, improving heart health and burning more calories for fat loss.

Support Joint Health Without High Impact:
Weighted vests provide resistance without the need for heavy external weights, making them gentler on joints while still offering strength-building benefits.

Improve Posture and Balance:
Wearing a weighted vest challenges core muscles, promoting better posture and balance, which are important for injury prevention and overall mobility.

If you want details on the weighted vest I purchased, message me ‚Äúvest‚Äù and I‚Äôll happily share! I don‚Äôt have an affiliation with the brand, I‚Äôm just excited about my purchase!

description:
This recipe and method is for a boneless ham that's approximately 1.5kg, this one is an Aussie Free Range Ham from @butcherboxsg. The method is the same for any sized ham, just draw out the cooking time.

1. The day before make the glaze. In a saucepan add
~2 cups brown sugar
~2 tblsp dijon mustard
~1 bottle real maple syrup
~a few sticks of cinnamon and star anise
Place on stove and bring to a simmer and whisk until sugar is dissolved, strain out the spices and chill in fridge overnight

2. Remove netting and cut off skin, be careful to leave the fat. 

3. Make incision half cm deep a cm apart diagonally across the fat, turn the ham and 90degrees across each incision slice a cm apart.

4. Push a clove into each square between each cut you made into the fat.

5. Place ham onto a wire rack on a baking tray. Put a sheet of baking paper and aluminium foil lining the tray for easy cleaning. Add water to the tray. About half cm deep, this will keep the ham moist and juicy and stop it from drying out during cooking and glazing.

6. Glaze ham with a pastry brush

7. Place ham in 120c preheated oven and set timer for 12 minutes.

8. When the timer goes off, glaze the ham again with a pastry brush. Reset timer for 12 minutes and keep repeating until ham has been in the oven for approximately 45minutes.

9. Check internal temperature of ham with a cake testing pin, by this time it should be warm

10. Raise heat to 160c and set time for 6 minutes, glaze every 6 minutes another 2 or 3 times until desired glaze colour is reached.

11. Remove from oven and rest for 30 minutes at room temperature, during this time you can pull out the cloves.

12. Slice and enjoy.

description:
There are so many reasons you should be lifting weights as a woman- especially if you are over age 40- but here are some of my top reasons. And NI! It won‚Äôt make you bulky! 

1. Prevent age-related muscle loss & maintain a higher metabolism. As we age, we lose muscle, UNLESS we do something to prevent it. That something is lifting weights & eating sufficient protein. Do this consistently, and you will lose less muscle as you age. Although not highly significantly, maintaining muscle mass does help to keep up your metabolism up.

2. As you lift you get stronger. You increase or maintain balance which helps to prevent injury. The weaker you get, the more likely you are to fall or injury yourself. Stay strong & avoid injury!

3. Lifting helps you feel better in your clothes and without them because you have improved muscle definition when you lift. Clothes fit better & your body looks more tight & toned. This often helps to improve confidence. Who doesn‚Äôt LOVE that?!

Lifting is essential for so many health reasons, these are just a few. If you aren‚Äôt currently lifting, you really should start! üí™üî• It‚Äôs not too late to join us for the Winter Shred. Message me ‚Äúshred‚Äù for details!

I made the conscious decision to slow down, to pause my work, to take a small step back social media and carefully chose the energy I allow into my space. Most importantly, I chose me‚Äîand it turned out to be the greatest gift I‚Äôve ever given myself üíñ

This year, I embarked on a profound journey of inner work. I delved deep into the core of who I am, uncovering truths and gaining insights that reshaped my understanding of myself. 
Any form of inner work can be challenging but it is also the most empowering investment one can make.

So here‚Äôs me, stepping into 2025 with eager anticipation, renewed energy, positivity, joy, immense gratitude and infinite peace ‚ú®

My intention for 2025? To spread love, inspire hope and share kindness abundantly. 
Let‚Äôs all do this together & make 2025 our best year yet ü©µ

description:
In my late 20s & early 30s I was a cardio junkie. Run & bike - on repeat. 

I enjoyed running for the most part because it was a great stress reliever for me, and while I was in great cardiovascular shape, there were many areas of my body that were neglected.

I had a weak core because I didn‚Äôt proritize core work after I had spent so much time running. Other than doing push ups most days, I neglected my upper body, again likely for the sake of time. My legs were strong, but my upper body was far from it. My fuel plan was carb-focused to give me energy for my runs. I know now that I should have been eating more protein!

Fitness is a journey, and for many years cardio was my thing. It is no longer, and I am glad to say that I feel more fit & confident than I ever did, even now in my 40s! 

Strength training has literally transformed my body & my attitude around fitness. I enjoy lifting & the results I have achieved- increased strength, improved muscle definition, clothes fitting better and overall just feeling stronger & more confident. 

If you are on the cardio band-wagon and looking for a change, take a leap with me. I‚Äôd love to get you started with strength training. You will love the results and never look back. 

Join the Winter Shred and start lifting with me. In just 6 short weeks you will be well on your way to a more fit & confident you!! For more details message me ‚Äúshred‚ÄùHURRY! We kickoff workouts Monday!

Are you screaming with me too? ü™Ω‚ú®

The moment i saw @setsunazaf posted this on her page (do check her out, she has such an amazing makeup & skincare collection!), I knew I had to add this into my collection ü•π

I remember sitting in front of the TV, waiting for Cardcaptor Sakura show on‚Ä¶ was it NTV7? Gosh, so much memories ü•∫ that feeling of flippin‚Äô through TV Guide on the newspaper to find out anime/cartoon‚Äôs air time, so much nostalgia! #justmillennialthings

Anywaysssss, I think @peripera_official nailed this collaboration with #CardcaptorSakura! Everything is so pretty, especially the engraving on the blush

They have eyeshadows, bb cushion, lip balm, lip tint and a blush for this collection, but here‚Äôs what I got:

ü™Ω Water Bear Tint in 12 - Sealing Power
ü™Ω Ink Mood Glowy Balm in 11 - Pink Guardian
ü™Ω Pure Blushed Custom Cheek in 05 - Dreamy Cherry

My fav is the lip balm! The colour is quite pigmented and super smooth on the lips. The tint is lovely, not drying but its a little too pigmented for me to use everyday, though it leaves a nice stain after wearing off. The blush is SOOOOO pretty. I only used it twice - not because its bad but I just do. not. want. to. ruin. it üòÇ It‚Äôs really ‚ú®shimmery‚ú® on the cheeks, giving a nice blush + highlight glow to the skin.

Honestly everything is really nice, I might want to get the whole balm collection! But the wallet doesn‚Äôt permit, so it‚Äôs time for the brain to takeover this decision, not the heart ü•∫

I purchased all of these myself on their official Shopee Mall store. Will be doing a separate carousel post on the swatches, do stay tuned üíñ

So, are you a Cardcaptor Sakura fan too? I wish some makeup brand would come out with a Chobits collection!! I‚Äôd seriously buy them all üòÇ
